cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image salient object detection using RGB-D data and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel adversarial learning framework, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of attention mechanisms and edge detection, which are common techniques in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks for end-to-end training, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
